1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,639
To add meaning to this self-imposed test, substitute the word company for world so it reads,

2
00:00:03,909 --> 00:00:09,639
What kind of company would this company be, if everyone in it were just like me?

3
00:00:11,509 --> 00:00:20,760
In similar fashion, ask yourself what kind of club, community, school, church would it be if everyone in it acted like you.

4
00:00:21,750 --> 00:00:30,119
Think, talk, act, live the way you want your subordinates to think, talk, act, live, and they will.

5
00:00:31,029 --> 00:00:36,679
Over a period of time, subordinates tend to become carbon copies of their chief.

6
00:00:36,949 --> 00:00:43,720
The simplest way to get high-level performance is to be sure the master copy is worth duplicating.

7
00:00:45,670 --> 00:00:48,840
Am I a Progressive Thinker Checklist?

8
00:00:49,269 --> 00:00:52,920
A. Do I think progressively toward my work?

9
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:53,720
1.

10
00:00:53,909 --> 00:00:58,519
Do I appraise my work with the how-can-we-do-it-better attitude?

11
00:00:58,549 --> 00:00:59,479
2.

12
00:00:59,670 --> 00:01:06,039
Do I praise my company, the people in it, and the products it sells at every possible opportunity?

13
00:01:06,039 --> 00:01:07,320
3.

14
00:01:07,670 --> 00:01:15,880
Are my personal standards with reference to the quantity and quality of my output higher now than three or six months ago?

15
00:01:15,880 --> 00:01:17,159
4.

16
00:01:17,429 --> 00:01:23,639
Am I setting an excellent example for my subordinates, associates, and others I work with?

17
00:01:24,469 --> 00:01:28,920
B. Do I think progressively toward my family?

18
00:01:29,190 --> 00:01:29,800
1.

19
00:01:30,230 --> 00:01:34,679
Is my family happier today than it was three or six months ago?

20
00:01:34,679 --> 00:01:35,639
2.

21
00:01:35,909 --> 00:01:40,199
Am I following a plan to improve my family's standard of living?

22
00:01:40,199 --> 00:01:41,159
3.

23
00:01:41,429 --> 00:01:47,000
Does my family have an ample variety of stimulating activities outside the home?

24
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,280
4.

25
00:01:48,549 --> 00:01:54,519
Do I set an example of a progressive, a supporter of progress for my children?

26
00:01:55,750 --> 00:01:59,960
C. Do I think progressively toward myself?

27
00:02:00,389 --> 00:02:01,000
1.

28
00:02:01,429 --> 00:02:07,559
Can I honestly say I am a more valuable person today than three or six months ago?

29
00:02:08,069 --> 00:02:08,679
2.

30
00:02:08,789 --> 00:02:14,519
Am I following an organized self-improvement program to increase my value to others?

31
00:02:14,519 --> 00:02:15,720
3.

32
00:02:15,989 --> 00:02:20,599
Do I have forward-looking goals for at least five years in the future?

33
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:21,720
4.

34
00:02:21,989 --> 00:02:26,679
Am I a booster in every organization or group to which I belong?

35
00:02:27,829 --> 00:02:32,280
D. Do I think progressively toward my community?

36
00:02:32,549 --> 00:02:33,079
1.

37
00:02:33,429 --> 00:02:39,559
Have I done anything in the past six months that I honestly feel has improved my community,

38
00:02:39,589 --> 00:02:42,599
neighborhood, churches, schools, etc.?

39
00:02:42,599 --> 00:02:44,119
2.

40
00:02:44,309 --> 00:02:50,440
Do I boost worthwhile community projects rather than object, criticize, or complain?

41
00:02:50,629 --> 00:02:51,639
3.

42
00:02:51,829 --> 00:02:57,559
Have I ever taken the lead in bringing about some worthwhile improvement in my community?

43
00:02:57,989 --> 00:02:58,599
Four.

44
00:02:58,789 --> 00:03:02,920
Do I speak well of my neighbors and fellow citizens?

45
00:03:04,629 --> 00:03:07,029
Leadership rule number four.
